I would maybe try `data |> group_by(participant) |> summarise()`, and then use the `n_distinct()` function to count how many "things" each person sees (e.g., [Chapter 4: Logistic MLM #example](https://uoepsy.github.io/lmm/04_log.html#example){target="_blank"}). 

